$ VIM variables: $HOME

`$HOME` belongs to the → development/vim/script/vimscript/variables#vim-three-special-dollar-variables[three special `$` variables], the other two being `$VIM` and `VIMRUNTIME`.

The value of `$HOME` is determined in → development/vim/sources/src/misc1_c#vim-src-misc1_init_homedir[`init_homedir()`] in → development/vim/sources/src/misc1_c[`misc1.c`] and stored in the
→ development/vim/sources/src/globals_h[global variable] `homedir`.
